      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is the difference between a front hook and a back hook?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A front hook adds a letter to the beginning of an existing word to form a new word (e.g., S + CAT = SCAT). A back hook adds a letter to the end (e.g., CAT + S = CATS). Front hooks are generally more surprising to opponents because players typically watch for back hooks like plurals." } },
